**Query #2**
--Query to group the data using a CASE statement.  This case statement describes the PTO analysis of each company based on the days given.
    SELECT company_name,
    CASE WHEN paid_time_off_days >=20 THEN 'high_pto'
    WHEN paid_time_off_days>=17 THEN 'above_avg_pto'
    WHEN paid_time_off_days>=14 THEN 'avg_pto'
    ELSE 'low_pto'
    END AS 'analysis'
    FROM fortune_companies
    WHERE industry='Finance';

| company_name | analysis |
| ------------ | -------- |
| Company E    | avg_pto  |
| Company L    | low_pto  |
| Company X    | low_pto  |
| Company EE   | low_pto  |

---
**Query #3**
--A HAVING clause.  Which industry has an average employee number above 20,000 and what are the avg employees for that industry?
    SELECT industry, AVG(employees) AS avg_employees_thousands
    FROM fortune_companies
    GROUP BY industry
    HAVING employees>=20000;

| industry           | avg_employees_thousands |
| ------------------ | ----------------------- |
| Energy             | 13950                   |
| Financials         | 255998                  |
| Retail             | 315685.71428571426      |
| Technology         | 218542.85714285713      |
| Telecommunications | 23750                   |

